### English Title:
Claims of Dismissal of Iraqi Army Spokesman Yahiya Rasul After Criticism of Syrian Interim President

### English Text Summary:
Social media accounts circulated claims about the dismissal of Yahiya Rasul, the former spokesman for the Iraqi army chief, following a video in which he criticized the interim president of Syria, Ahmad al-Shara. This speculation arose amid discussions in Iraq regarding rapprochement with Syria after a meeting between Iraqi Prime Minister Mohammed Shia' al-Sudani and al-Shara in Qatar. The claims were found to be misleading, as Rasul had already left his position in January, replaced by Saleh al-Nauman. The video in question was not recent and was part of an interview from December 2024, during a time of conflict involving Syrian opposition forces.

